Package com.graphql_java_generator.plugin.language

Interface Field

All Known Implementing Classes:
FieldImpl
public interface Field
This interface describes one field of one objet type (or interface...). It aims to be simple enough, so that the Velocity template can easily generated ths fields from it.
For instance: 
 name: String!
is a Field of name 'name', type 'String', and is mandatory. or 
 appearsIn: [Episode!]!
is a Field of name 'appearsIn', type 'Episode', is a list, is mandatory and its items are mandatory.
Author:
EtienneSF

    • getGraphQLTypeName

      java.lang.String getGraphQLTypeName()
      The type of this field, as defined in the GraphQL schema. This type is either the type of the field (if it's not a list), or the type of the items in the list (if it's a list)

    • isId

      boolean isId()
      Indicates whether this field is an id or not. It's used in PluginMode#SERVER mode to add the javax.persistence annotations for the id fields. Default value is false. This field is set to true for GraphQL fields which are of 'ID' type.

    • getInputParameters

    • isMandatory

      boolean isMandatory()
      Is this field mandatory? If this field is a list, then mandatory indicates whether the list itself is mandatory, or may be nullable

    • isItemMandatory

      boolean isItemMandatory()
      Indicates whether the item in the list are not nullable, or not. Only used if this field is a list.

    • getDefaultValue

      java.lang.Object getDefaultValue()
      Contains the default value.. Only used if this field is an input parameter. For enums, it contains the label of the enum, not the value of the enum.

    • getRelation
